  &lt;p id="rbjbXp"&gt;Netflix is constantly looking for its next big franchise hit — a new &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/stranger-things"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Stranger Things&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;or &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2019/12/20/21026537/the-witcher-netflix-review-henry-cavill"&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Witcher&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;. &lt;/em&gt;And the trailer for &lt;a href="https://www.theyoungfolks.com/books/150906/netflix-shadow-and-bone-grishaverse-characters-explained/"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Shadow and Bone&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;teases that the upcoming fantasy series could be next. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="rklqUJ"&gt;The first trailer for Netflix’s adaptation of the series showcases the series’ main protagonist, Alina, a map maker who discovers that she harbors a special power that can prevent the world from being swallowed up in darkness threatened by a terrifying sea-of-sorts called the Fold. &lt;/p&gt;
